    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\nFrom [the vector attributes documentation](https://docs.generic-mapping-tools.org/latest/grdvector.html#vector-attributes):\r\n\r\n> +g[fill] sets the vector head fill [Default fill is used, which may be no fill]. Turn off vector head fill by not appending a fill. Some modules have a separate -Gfill option and if used will select the fill as well.\r\n\r\n> +p[pen] sets the vector pen attributes. If no pen is appended then the head outline is not drawn. [Default pen is half the width of stem pen, and head outline is drawn]. Above, we used +p2p,orange. The vector stem attributes are controlled by -W.\r\n\r\nHowever, it seems that the `-G` (`-W`) option is mandatory, even if `+g` (`+p`) was given. Reading the above, it seems to me that `-G` (`-W`) should be optional in this case.\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/sh\r\n\r\ngmt begin arrow_head_pen\r\n    gmt grdmath -R-2/2/-2/2 -I0.1 X Y R2 NEG EXP X MUL = z.nc\r\n    gmt grdmath z.nc DDX = dzdx.nc\r\n    gmt grdmath z.nc DDY = dzdy.nc\r\n    gmt grdvector dzdx.nc dzdy.nc -JX12c/0 -Baf -BWSen -I0.3 -Q0.4+e+n0.4+ggreen+p1,red+h0\r\ngmt end show\r\nrm z.nc dzdx.nc dzdy.nc\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Error message**\r\n\r\n```\r\ngrdvector [ERROR]: Must specify at least one of -G, -W, -C\r\n```\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* Operating system: Linux x86_64 5.14.16-arch1-1 with GCC 11.1.0\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`): 6.2.0\r\n",
